content: An excellent puzzle game. After you "complete" the game there is a second world which forces you to replay the older levels and think outside the box. Well worth the time and money to experience this game.
Fun push block puzzler. Take it in small doses for best results.
Controls aren't very good, but the puzzles are good. I only wish they added an alternative control scheme.

I absolutely adore this game. It's cute, short, and solid. Excellent puzzle design and overall feel. I love puzzle games that teach you how to play without telling you. And I love puzzle games with secrets that don't tell you about the secrets. This is a great game.
Really enjoyable, surprisingly complex game (especially when you try for butterflies and the Mirror World). Also just so cute! Make sure to hug a snowman.
Good game
Bravo.
Fresh
Wonderful and calming animation and graphics. Challenging puzzles too! Exactly what I was looking for.
So far, so good. I could see it getting tedious after a while but its kind of like mindful colouring
It's so nice and cute game!!! :D And at the same time it's an interesting and fairly challenging puzzle game. Though somewhat small. A true masterpiece in it's own way.
Beautiful, relaxing, smart little game.
A beautiful sokoban with an immense amount of polish, charm, and surprisingly intuitive mobile controls. Often a nice challenge but not punitive. Only narcs don't hug every snowman.

Cute! Puzzles are really good, too; years later, when filling-in forms which are supposed to help me find good games, I still use A Good Snowman is Hard to Build as an example of a game I like, but unfortunately there doesn't seem to be any other game like it out there.

It's mostly a great game. But the way things are (or aren't) communicated to the player is in my opinion not clever but a mistake. There are for instance the butterflies - the meaning of which I had to look up. Or the dream sequences - which I again had to look up. Also, the endgame reminds me of the one in "The Witness" in that unlike the initial part of the game, it's not primarily challenging but just incredibly cumbersome and time consuming.
Lovely game! So excited by the next one.
Awesome game
Good game. I Still don't know what your actual goals are here and it seems that story about this monster in game doesn't actually exist. So I will rate it 4 stars for now.

Some spoilers below. Really enjoyable game. The simple concept belies the challenging puzzles, and the huggable snowmen make for a great presentation. Spoilers: I took 1 mark away for the confusing 2nd part of the game. The destruction & rebuilding of the snowmen sadly gets tedious. Great game otherwise.

Great logic game with very nice graphics. Altought the mechanics/principles are simple, some puzzles are really tough and make you brain worl full speed. And when you think the game is over there is another layer of puzzles awaiting. Simply great game for both kids and adults.
A lot of love went into this game.

It's cute and the puzzles are pretty zen. Happy to see some free form solution optimization. Felt a little light... Not much variation on the theme, and was able to wrap everything up the day after i got it. Also, stability could use some work... Lots of crashes.
Great level design. fun gameplay
good
Lol crashing every 2 minutes
Very nice puzzle game. Me and my kids love it
Of course I would like this, as I like Sokoban. But it's well done too in all aspects. Check out other games like Cosmic Express and Dr Biology. Hope we'll see more from the author.
Vry gd
Good and challenging.
The perfect puzzle game. Can be completed by a puzzle novice, but has more to offer for experts.

Very cute and clean graphics, none of the puzzles have stumped me for more 
than a couple minutes yet though

This game is so loving and sweet. Even when I was stumped by certain 
puzzles, I didn't feel frustrated, which is rare for me in a puzzle game. I 
love that there is a hugging mechanic. And without giving anything away, 
the, let's say "new game +" revealed just how masterful this team is at 
creating puzzles. Really amazing charming work. I had a delicious few hours 
and I would 100% support another run of levels, or whatever else they do 
next ❤
Elegant puzzles, slick controls, a lot of charm and character, rewarding and challenging in just the right balance. A great game worth anyone's time.
One of the best puzzles games for Android you will find.
Quick responding dev and a great game. Thank you.
replyContent: Hi Dylan, this app does have family library sharing enabled. If you're having a problem with that, you should contact Google rather than leaving a negative review here.

content: Good puzzles, nice art style
Love the simple brilliance of this game... Always good for a replay at Christmas...
Lovely game. Wish it had a little hint system; but even when I'm frustrated trying to find a solution, it feels more like the game's gently teasing me than setting up pretentious roadblocks.
Don't let the cuteness fool you. These puzzles get really challenging really fast!
The little monster hugs the snowmen!

I find the game so beutiful! It. And it's beyond cute, it is adorable!  The story of a little monster that build snowmans (that you can hug which was so cool for me!) It's a unique game and so creative! And for me, the moral of the story being that if a little monster can help snow become snowmans and bring them to life, you can do much more, this became one of my favorites game! Thank you Drakek for this master-piece!!
Adorable I loved playing it and I recommend it to anyone who wants a cute, fun, easy to play game
Utterly charming game in the same vein as Monument Valley. Cracking spacial awareness puzzles and lovely atmospherics.. Download and enjoy!

I had an opportunity to play this at MoPop, and loved it so much I purchased it for my Android. It's the only game I've ever purchased for my phone. What I value about it is the opportunity to problem solve in order to advance. The adorable touches (such as the opportunity to hug each snowperson) are a clincher in enjoying this game. Well done, you have this stubborn non-gamer resolving to follow your company/developers to discover what else you might produce. Only negative is that it sometimes kicks me out, but easy to reopen and it always remembers where I was at. Whew! I seriously adore this game, thank you.
The best kind of puzzle game, simple concept that has challenging implications. And clear, cute design.
amazing puzzles and difficulty curve, as usual for draknek. it crashed several times, but with no lost data.
A cute mellow puzzler with hidden depth and oodles of polish.
Lovely and unique puzzle game! Charming art, nice sound, great animation and interaction.
Great puzzle game! The puzzles take thought and work but never stump you too permanently.
Adorable, relaxing, beautiful puzzle game.
Lovely little game. Hugs alone worth the full price of the game.
I have really enjoyed this. I highly recommend it!
Very challenging!
Cute. Nothing else to say. It is also a good game, too!
This game is a challenge but the music and general feeling of it keep it from being frustrating when I get stuck.

Just the visuals and the animation make an amusing game full of eye candy, but then there is an even cuter concept on top of it. The simple yet difficult task of building a snowman is even more rewarding when you get to hug their cute faces
Really polished and original puzzle game.
Hard to describe, and unlike any in its field. Resonates and leaves an impression in your psyche.

I enjoy transport puzzles, and this might be the best one I've ever played. The puzzles are very well crafted, and it has a lovely style. There's some very intriguing depth to it, but I don't want to say too much.
Love the scenario and music.
Cute game with seriously challenging puzzles!

This game is a very engaging puzzler in which you help an adorable creature build snowmen friends. I don't think I've ever wanted to just reach in and hug a video game character before. In addition to the excellent design and unique premise, the puzzles are challenging and the game saves your progress reliably. My only suggestion to improve this game would be to make it longer.
This is a delightful game, but on my lg g5 it crashes randomly.  Other than that I would recommend the game to anyone.

There were several aesthetic audiovisual choices made here that elevate an elegantly simple puzzle game into a zenlike snowman smorgasbord. Excellent freedom in the progression system that emphasises that the player can proceed at their own pace, in their own direction. Clearly a great deal of thought and care has been put into each detail of this delightful experience.

The game crashed many times during play (but didn't lose my progress), and there seems to be a disconnect between the dream world progress trackers.  The one with snowballs indicates 100% but the dream world not showing snowballs shows lower progress.  I'm not even sure why there are two versions of the dream world.  In any event, the game was very enjoyable.  I certainly got my money's worth.
Sooooo good!
A great game with some tricky first phase puzzles and a really interesting second phase...
Solid little game
Challenging puzzles, delightful graphics.
Very fun
The pacing was just right and I really enjoyed the atmosphere.
When i played it on my one plus x.. Sometimes the game crash suddenly.. It is really jarring.. I hope you can fix it so i can gladly give it a five star.. Thx
Very polished and relaxing game, great puzzles, just does crash frequently
This is a nice puzzle game. Very similar to Sokoban, but you have to control the size of your snowballs as they roll over snow, plus nice graphics, music, and interactive environment.
Can't believe it only has 1000 downloads.  Great game well paced crashes sometimes but not a problem. Music a bit too ethereal after a while but otherwise really well thought out and enjoyable
Great game
Only issue is frequent crashes, but game picks up where you left off.  Hope they fix this
Totally fun
I love  it
Relaxing and Challenging
Its a amazing puzzle game
Great take on the "Crate Moving"  sokobahn style puzzlers.
Cool game with fun puzzles!
Superb game on all fronts - right level of difficulty - great graphics fun. A1 game.
Great game
This puzzle game is fun for kids and adults without being too challenging that younger players need constant help. Worth every penny!
Heh... Get it? GOODness... Seriously though, more than one thousand people should be at the pleasure of enjoying this amazing game.
The gameplay is straightforward and challenging, but what sets this game apart is the tremendous attention to detail and the sense of pure simplicity in how it plays.

This is a game that everyone can truly enjoy, the puzzles are surprisingly challenging despite having a very simple concept, however, the relaxing atmosphere and satisfaction after completing each challenge just leaves you wanting more. The perfect game to get yourself lost in!
Lovely :)
Great game, very nice graphics and background music, good puzzles. Did get the occasional crash and it's a bit short for the price.
More levels please!
Brilliant game very satisfying to play
Fun game with nice depth. Very satisfying exploration of one puzzle space. No filler or repeated puzzles.
Addicted
I play this game on Shield Tablet. I frequently find myself on the homepage. Game quits for no reason.
Very difficult
It is so fun I love it because it doesn't snow that much in England and I'm not good at making a snowman 😁
A fun game. Some of the puzzles really made me think.
Nice puzzler
Great relaxing game, some of the puzzles are difficult!
It was really cute and worth buying, but... I beat the main game in about an hour and the post game in maybe another 2. Plus it kept crashing. Thankfully no progress is lost when it does.

I open the game to a blank screen the same colour as the dark maze. Have to shut down phone & restart for maze, but then he's on the bench hemmed in by a snowball so Im perpetually stuck between sleep-maze & awake maze inable to move. Huh?
replyContent: Hi, sorry you're having problems! Can you email hello@agoodsnowman.com with screenshots please? This is the first I've heard of this problem and I'd like to help.

content: I had thought it would make a good mobile game!
What an adorable game. Fun puzzles!

The look and feel is perfect. Puzzles are challenging and enjoyable. And best of all the game doesn't need a bunch of stupid extraneous permissions. It asks to rate it, but only when you sit on a bench for long enough. It's cute instead of irritating.
This game is a nice combination of thinky and relaxing.

Lots of fun and plenty of puzzles to really work your brain. Wish the controls were a touch better, but the undo button makes errors go away. Only thing this is missing is Play Games integration for leaderboard and achievements, along with cloud sync so you can pick up your progress on a different device
£4 that just cost me
Very cute characters, great mind bending puzzles
Cute graphics, interesting puzzles, calm music

Enchanting game and unlike anything I've come across recently. Felt almost like a little art film. Four stars rather than five as it kept crashing.  Keep watching after you have solved the final puzzle!
It may just be me but personally I found it way too hard. Barely made it past the fifth room before I gave up in frustration. Please make like an easy medium hard thing or a hints button.
Given the price, decided to get a refund after it crashed twice in quick succession. Lovely game but needs the bugs ironing out or the price dropped.
I play games that have an outstanding art style and this game definitely does not disappoint. Gameplay is great as well.
The gameplay screen is all messed up, tiles repeating and overlapping. Is this tablet only? Please fix
replyContent: Hi Tanner, this should be fixed now with the latest update. Sorry for the inconvenience, hope you enjoy the game!

content: Runs fantastic, looks great, nice and hard i am having problems with the controls but that's just me
Game did not work on my moto x
replyContent: Hi Katie, this should be fixed now with the latest update. Sorry for the inconvenience, hope you enjoy the game!

content: It's so calming. I see nothing wrong with it

Well done.  I played through it in one go.  It crashed a couple times (Galaxy Note 5) but never lost progress.  Can't wait to see the next one, or more levels.  Do yourself a favor, and sit on a bench :)
If I could I would gift this to everyone in my address book for Christmas. Wonderful game, beautifully designed - it is aesthetically brilliant, mechanically sound and joyously programmed.
Snowkoban.
So fun!

I like this little black creature named every snowman and give them a big hug everytime he built it. The difficulty of this puzzle is just enough for me to keep on trying and not feeling frustrated. I like this game so far!

Top marks fully earnt to the makers of this app. A Genuinely great and unique game with a silky smooth tone to it. I love the music to it too. A really feel good fun factor to this app. No in app purchases either, so worth paying the £3.99 for it.
I adore this game so much. Wonderful atmosphere, combined with genuinely original and challenging (but fair) puzzles -- and some nice surprises. Total A+.
The puzzles are hard but interesting.I love walking around the world and interacting with it and it was a longer game than I first thought!
I think I value friendship more having played this game =)
Perfect puzzle game
Awesome ambient and really challenging puzzle game
Lovely and calm puzzle game where you build a ⛄, which, as it turns out, is fairly tricky!
The puzzles are nice, the visuals and animations are stunning.
